## Yellow follow-ups (non-blocking)

1. `.localhost` suffix branch is only transitively covered by the `tenant.local` test. Recommend adding `https://api.dev.localhost` to `check-production-smoke-guard.mjs` for explicit suffix-branch coverage.
2. Inner-label check only matches `staging`/`stage`/`test`/`testing`; `tenant.dev.example.com` would pass. Probably intentional (over-matching carries false-positive cost) but worth flagging if the user wants belt-and-braces.
3. `.github/workflows/production-smoke.yml` does not pass `PRODUCTION_SMOKE_ALLOW_NON_PRODUCTION_HOSTS` through (so CI cannot fake a Green) — this is a feature, not a bug, but the runbook could note that staging rehearsal from GitHub UI requires local invocation.
4. New error message interpolates `hostname` into the failure text; `redact()` only handles configured secrets, so a hostile hostname containing the token would still partially leak. Not reachable today (hostname comes from URL parsing, not user input) but worth tracking.

